      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LAURIE'S FERRARI (8) goes very well here starting 13 times for seven wins and four minors. Missed the frame latest (25.18) when fourth over 431m at this track in a Grade 5. Looks well placed and should feature. RAZOR'S SHINE (1) was below best last time but prior to that was narrowly beaten when fourth (19.68) in a Grade 5 at this track. Good beginner and aided by the inside draw. Expected to do much better this time. KIANDO PIPER (3) had been going along well winning a Grade 5 three back then placing at this track before missing the frame latest when fifth (30.68) at Dubbo. Safe beginner and drawn well close to the inside. Can hit the frame this time. URBAN BOY (2) made it two minor placings on the trot when beaten third (20.08) in a Grade 5 at this track last time out.",
